istic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Henry","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["A perennially popular given name, of Continental Germanic origin, from <i>haim</i> ‘home’ + <i>rīc</i> ‘power, ruler’. It was an Old French name, adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to Britain. It has been borne by eight kings of England. Not until the 17th century did the form <i>Henry</i> (as opposed to   Harry  ) become the standard vernacular form, mainly under the influence of the Latin form <i>Henricus</i> and French <i>Henri</i>."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Lady Henry de Annadio was born in 1295, in Clackmannanshire, Scotland. She had at least 1 son with Henry De Annadio Sheriff of Clackmannanshire."},"et":{"1295–":"1295–Surnud","–1350":"–1350","1323–Male":"1323–Surnud","1295–Female":"1295–Surnud","1323":"1323","1295":"1295","1350":"1350","Clackmannanshire, Scotland":"Clackmannanshire, Scotland","Sauchie, Clackmannanshire, Scotland":"Sauchie, Clackmannanshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1295–":"1295–Kuollut","–1350":"–1350","1323–Male":"1323–Kuollut","1295–Female":"1295–Kuollut","1323":"1323","1295":"1295","1350":"1350","Clackmannanshire, Scotland":"Clackmannanshire, Scotland","Sauchie, Clackmannanshire, Scotland":"Sauchie, Clackmannanshire, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1295–":"1295–Décédée","–1350":"–1350","1323–Male":"1323–Décédé","1295–Female":"1295–Décédée","1323":"1323","1295":"1295","1350":"1350","Clackmannanshire, Scotland":"Clackmannanshire, Écosse","Sauchie, Clackmannanshire, Scotland":"Sauchie, Clackmannanshire, Écosse, Royaume-U